I walk around like a victim?

15:25.120 --> 15:26.770
I don't think I walk
around like a victim.

15:26.840 --> 15:28.729
Do you think I'm
a negotiator?

15:28.800 --> 15:30.609
Like I'm constantly
trying to keep the peace,

15:30.680 --> 15:32.364
even if there's no
peace to be kept?

15:32.440 --> 15:35.523
I mean, that's actually
written in a sentence.

15:35.600 --> 15:37.887
I mean, that's just bad sentence
construction, in my opinion.

15:37.960 --> 15:43.251
Am I living in a shell of insecurity
and approval-seeking?

15:44.040 --> 15:45.166
I don't know.

15:46.200 --> 15:47.326
You know what?

15:48.960 --> 15:50.769
Thank you for this.

15:57.400 --> 15:58.686
(SIGHS)

16:03.680 --> 16:05.967
- Hi.
- Mom.

16:06.040 --> 16:07.041
Hi.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.401
People are going to think
you're my boy toy.

16:10.480 --> 16:12.721
Don't say that.
Shall we?

16:14.440 --> 16:17.523
It's better for you
at room temperature.

16:21.080 --> 16:24.129
So, I brought you something.

16:32.200 --> 16:34.248
Huh.
Yeah, I remember that book.

16:34.320 --> 16:35.970
It's funny, I don't.

16:36.080 --> 16:38.242
You don't?
Well, you should keep it.

16:38.320 --> 16:40.129
- So...
- Mom.

16:40.600 --> 16:42.364
- What?
- Why?

16:42.480 --> 16:45.802
Your father was running around

16:45.880 --> 16:48.360
with every 25-year-old
coat check girl in the city.

16:48.440 --> 16:49.805
Mom.

16:49.880 --> 16:51.848
And you really needed
to talk to somebody.

16:51.920 --> 16:54.048
Relax. She didn't use
your real name.

16:54.120 --> 16:56.441
You were like Robert or something.

16:56.520 --> 16:57.851
- Rob.
- it's Rick.

16:57.920 --> 16:59.684
- Rick!
- Rick.

17:00.600 --> 17:01.601
So you read it?

17:01.720 --> 17:04.769
According to this,
Rick is a total disaster.

17:05.599 --> 17:08.365
You do realize that Rick
now owns a successful business

17:08.440 --> 17:10.920
and has employees
who come to him with their problems.

17:11.319 --> 17:13.321
- Mmm-hmm.
- Rick has a beautiful girlfriend

17:13.400 --> 17:16.131
- whom he loves.
- Mmm-hmm.

17:16.200 --> 17:18.726
Carter, please tell me this book is
not the reason you brought me here.

17:19.280 --> 17:20.724
Oh, no. It's not.

17:24.640 --> 17:26.926
Put that on a good hanger
for me, will you.

17:27.680 --> 17:29.409
All of our hangers
are quite good, sir.

17:29.480 --> 17:31.084
Ha, that's cute.

17:32.880 --> 17:34.041
MAITRE D:
Right this way, sir.

17:34.120 --> 17:36.327
I pulled the big gun out tonight.

17:36.400 --> 17:37.765
Having dinner with my son.

17:37.840 --> 17:40.525
Mmm, crab.
You know they self-amputate?

17:45.440 --> 17:47.090
Hey, buddy. Look.

17:49.240 --> 17:50.241
Shit!

17:50.320 --> 17:51.845
- Shall I open the wine?
- No!

17:51.920 --> 17:53.490
Yes. Sit down.

17:54.920 --> 17:56.490
Sit, Dad.

17:58.560 --> 18:00.688
Forget it. I'll go.

18:01.160 --> 18:02.286
Fine.

18:03.600 --> 18:05.011
You leave, he wins.

18:06.040 --> 18:10.090
Right. You go. I cleared a very busy
evening to have dinner with my son.

18:11.280 --> 18:12.486
Like I didn't?

18:15.160 --> 18:16.571
(DISHES CLATTERING)

18:22.760 --> 18:25.923
You've destroyed this evening.
What have you done?

18:26.040 --> 18:27.804
This is ridiculous!

18:27.880 --> 18:29.769
Is it? I don't know.
Look around you.

18:29.840 --> 18:31.285
The building is still standing.

18:31.360 --> 18:33.567
You're both in the same room

18:33.640 --> 18:37.122
and somehow the universe
hasn't folded in on itself.

18:37.200 --> 18:39.771
Holy shit. Now, I brought
you both here tonight,

18:39.840 --> 18:41.763
because you've turned
a nine-year marriage

18:41.840 --> 18:43.888
into a hundred-year war.

18:44.640 --> 18:46.961
And I am officially over it.

18:48.040 --> 18:51.123
We're playing by new rules now.
Okay?

18:51.200 --> 18:53.885
Trey is getting married.
There is going to be a wedding.

18:53.960 --> 18:55.962
Now, you don't have to pay for it,
you don't have to organize it,

18:56.040 --> 19:00.602
you don't even have to enjoy it.
All you have to do is show up, be civil,

19:00.680 --> 19:04.605
and for one night,
just shut the fuck up.

19:04.680 --> 19:05.681
The drama.

19:05.760 --> 19:07.125
A pain in the ass, he is.

19:07.200 --> 19:09.328
On, my God. (STAMMERING)

19:09.400 --> 19:10.925
You actually agree
on something.

19:11.000 --> 19:13.480
That's fantastic.
This is a great start, you guys.

19:13.560 --> 19:17.281
You sit here, you talk.
You have a good time together.

19:17.360 --> 19:19.840
I ordered the tasting menu
and I paid for it,

19:20.560 --> 19:22.085
so bon appétit!

19:24.240 --> 19:28.529
Oh, and FYI,
I've never been to Honduras.

19:46.880 --> 19:48.120
Have you had your face done?

19:59.280 --> 20:02.966
I gotta tell you, what you did,
that took some balls.

20:03.040 --> 20:04.246
Well, thank you.

20:04.320 --> 20:08.211
Yeah, honestly, I should have
straightened them out years ago.

20:08.280 --> 20:11.204
- It felt good.
- All right. So, what's next?

20:11.280 --> 20:12.441
Well,

20:14.200 --> 20:16.726
full speed ahead.
You plan the wedding you want, Trey.

20:16.800 --> 20:18.689
- Awesome!
- Oh, by the way,

20:18.760 --> 20:20.683
we don't want Morn and Dad
paying for anything, so don't ask.

20:20.760 --> 20:23.445
- Okay.
- Can Kieko's family help out?

20:23.520 --> 20:24.567
- Um...
- Because I'd be happy

20:24.640 --> 20:26.244
to chip in, as well.

20:26.320 --> 20:28.402
- Really?
- Yeah, of course.

20:28.480 --> 20:33.042
(STAMMERING) Dude,
I can't thank you enough.

20:33.120 --> 20:36.806
I mean it. Just for all of it.

20:37.720 --> 20:41.441
Well, it's how it should be.

20:42.720 --> 20:44.370
This stuff, it's...

20:46.680 --> 20:49.206
it doesn't have to be so
complicated, does it?

20:50.200 --> 20:53.682
All I'm saying is don't leave the
classroom without putting shorts on

20:53.760 --> 20:55.489
over those shorts.
Okay?

21:01.640 --> 21:04.928
Hey, so do male strippers
work here or...

21:05.000 --> 21:07.765
Ah, that's Herve,
the French spinning instructor.

21:07.840 --> 21:10.764
Herve? Aren't the French
supposed to be about

21:10.840 --> 21:12.842
leaving a little something
to the imagination?

21:13.360 --> 21:14.850
What's with the surprise visit?

21:14.960 --> 21:19.966
Oh, well, I got you a little something.
I think you might like it.

21:22.800 --> 21:24.802
Oh, my God.

21:26.200 --> 21:27.850
No! No, no.

21:27.920 --> 21:29.968
Oh, my God, Carter.

21:30.640 --> 21:31.926
No, no.

21:32.040 --> 21:34.884
I'm sorry, it's a...
This is a...

21:34.960 --> 21:36.610
It's just a key.

21:36.680 --> 21:37.886
It's a key?
Oh, my God.

21:37.960 --> 21:39.086
It's just a key.

21:40.720 --> 21:43.485
I mean, you said you wanted
a key for my apartment.

21:43.560 --> 21:45.289
Right, right, right.

21:45.360 --> 21:48.045
- Right! You scared me.
- Sorry.

21:48.640 --> 21:49.721
It's an antique chain.

21:49.800 --> 21:52.485
- It's really nice.
- Do you see the beads?

22:00.440 --> 22:01.521
What's that?

22:02.880 --> 22:05.565
Your step-mom sent this over
with instructions to hang it.

22:06.040 --> 22:07.929
- What is it?
- it's her painting.

22:08.000 --> 22:09.001
She paints?

22:09.080 --> 22:12.163
- Apparently, yes.
- Okay. Take it down.

22:12.240 --> 22:14.242
Oh, no. I can't.

22:14.320 --> 22:17.085
She threatened to sell the place
to Dunkin' Donuts if we did that.

22:21.760 --> 22:24.331
Is that Sondra? What do you
think she's crying about?

22:24.400 --> 22:25.890
The painting she's in.

22:25.960 --> 22:28.281
- (KNOCKING ON WINDOW)
- Hi!

22:28.360 --> 22:30.488
The homeless are getting
so aggressive these days.

22:30.560 --> 22:31.721
What the hell?

22:34.400 --> 22:37.847
- Hello.
- Hi! Whitegrass. Is that Indian?

22:37.960 --> 22:39.007
No.

22:39.080 --> 22:42.846
Is it the healthy drink
that you have with ginger sometimes?

22:42.920 --> 22:44.809
- That's wheatgrass.
- Oh, yeah.

22:46.280 --> 22:49.807
- That's so funny.
- So what are you doing here?

22:49.880 --> 22:53.089
Yeah, well, listen.
I realized something

22:53.160 --> 22:55.686
after you left the other day
and I had to tell you.

22:56.640 --> 22:59.450
Oh, thank you. No, it's fine.
Yeah, I'm fine.

22:59.520 --> 23:01.170
It turns out seeing you

23:02.720 --> 23:05.246
and seeing your book,
it kind of got me going.

23:05.360 --> 23:07.522
And I confronted my parents,
and set them straight

23:07.600 --> 23:09.568
and showed them
who's boss.

23:09.640 --> 23:10.846
Really?

23:11.480 --> 23:14.324
Yeah, really.
I'm great, actually. So...

23:15.640 --> 23:17.642
Definitely not that
kid from your book.

23:17.720 --> 23:18.721
Well, of course you aren't.

23:18.800 --> 23:21.690
You were a kid back then.
Which got me to thinking.

23:22.320 --> 23:25.369
There's no current research
about people like you.

23:25.440 --> 23:27.249
- People like me?
- ACODs.

23:27.320 --> 23:29.561
Adult Children of Divorce.

23:29.640 --> 23:30.641
That's mine.

23:30.760 --> 23:33.843
I'm getting in touch with
the other subjects from my book

23:33.960 --> 23:36.122
for a follow-up.
A sequel.

23:36.640 --> 23:40.690
A 20-year study of a generation
unique to the American landscape.

23:40.760 --> 23:44.003
Carter, do you realize
you were the least parented,

23:44.080 --> 23:47.323
least nurtured generation ever?

23:47.400 --> 23:49.801
Sorry. I'm going
to be in another book?

23:49.880 --> 23:50.927
- Yes.
- No.

23:51.000 --> 23:52.570
- Oh, yes.
- No, no, no, no, no.

23:52.640 --> 23:54.608
- What are you afraid of?
- I'm not afraid of anything.

23:54.680 --> 23:55.841
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)
- I can assure you of that.

23:56.000 --> 23:58.207
Carter, listen to me.
When you were a little boy,

23:58.280 --> 24:00.408
your parents turned to you
for emotional support.

24:00.480 --> 24:02.767
They thrust you
into the center of their divorce.

24:02.840 --> 24:05.446
In my book,
I called it "parentification."

24:05.520 --> 24:09.525
But look at you now, as an adult.
You're well-adjusted,

24:09.600 --> 24:12.080
you're successful,
you're responsible.

24:12.160 --> 24:13.446
Look, you're the owner
of the Wheatgrass.

24:13.520 --> 24:14.760
Whitegrass.

24:14.840 --> 24:17.605
You're dressing sharp,
you have a great haircut.

24:17.680 --> 24:20.081
I want to tell that story, Carter.

24:21.360 --> 24:24.489
- It is a better story.
- Infinitely. It's inspiring.

24:24.560 --> 24:26.961
I can set the record straight
about "Rick"?

24:27.040 --> 24:31.170
Now, I'm free most days, but Friday
at 1:00 is really good for me.

24:31.280 --> 24:32.850
- How about you?
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)

24:32.920 --> 24:35.571
- Can you give me just a second?
- Sure.

24:36.440 --> 24:37.566
Hey, Sondra, what's up?

24:37.640 --> 24:39.847
SONDRA: Hey, how is
the father-son retreat going?

24:40.520 --> 24:41.726
Um, what?

24:41.800 --> 24:43.006
When's your tee time?

24:43.080 --> 24:44.206
My...

24:45.600 --> 24:47.409
Where are you?

24:47.480 --> 24:50.086
I'm at my sorority
reunion at Cornell.

24:50.880 --> 24:52.211
You went to Cornell?

24:52.280 --> 24:54.089
Shocking, Carter.
Put your father on.

24:55.840 --> 25:00.289
Oh, my God, JJ, you look amazing!
You're so skinny.

25:01.080 --> 25:02.081
What?

25:03.200 --> 25:04.929
<i>Hello?</i>

25:05.600 --> 25:09.002
(STAMMERING)
He's at the pro shop.

25:09.080 --> 25:10.161
Well, go get him.

25:10.240 --> 25:12.561
I... I can't.

25:12.640 --> 25:13.846
Just yell his name.

25:13.920 --> 25:15.490
I'm getting my clubs cleaned.

25:15.560 --> 25:17.801
Can I have him call you right back?

25:17.880 --> 25:19.609
<i>Oh, my God, forget it.</i>

25:19.720 --> 25:23.122
Just tell him I look really good, that
I look better than a lot of people here.

25:23.200 --> 25:24.770
Okay?

25:26.120 --> 25:28.726
- Who was that?
- On the phone?

25:28.800 --> 25:32.964
- Yeah.
- My chef. He just needs peppers...

25:34.160 --> 25:36.447
Why don't I clear
the whole day on Friday?

25:36.520 --> 25:37.521
Okay.

25:37.640 --> 25:40.246
I'm so happy to be working
with you again, Carter.

25:40.320 --> 25:41.810
Thank you.

25:45.600 --> 25:47.125
(PHONE RINGING)

25:49.000 --> 25:50.047
Hey.

25:50.120 --> 25:51.531
Have you talked to Dad?

25:51.640 --> 25:53.563
Yeah. He's home sick.

25:53.640 --> 25:54.721
So you talked to him?

25:54.800 --> 25:58.043
Yeah, we were supposed to go tux
shopping for the greatest tux ever,

25:58.160 --> 26:00.288
and he called
and said he was shitting fire.

26:01.520 --> 26:03.284
All right, thanks.

26:22.920 --> 26:24.001
Dad?

26:25.160 --> 26:26.321
Hello?

26:33.560 --> 26:34.721
Hello?

26:41.000 --> 26:42.126
Pop?

26:44.600 --> 26:45.726
Hello?

26:53.720 --> 26:55.882
(MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE)

26:56.760 --> 26:58.444
Oh, Jesus!

27:00.280 --> 27:01.281
(SCREAMS)

27:02.080 --> 27:03.081
Mom!

27:03.160 --> 27:04.446
No!

27:09.080 --> 27:11.082
Jesus! Shit! Shit!

27:11.160 --> 27:12.605
I should have turned on the alarm.

27:24.440 --> 27:25.441
Carter!

27:25.520 --> 27:27.409
Carter! Hey!

27:27.880 --> 27:29.370
Jesus.

27:37.960 --> 27:39.200
Spring.

27:42.080 --> 27:46.608
And shoulders. Good. Relax.

27:50.080 --> 27:51.366
I need to talk to you!

27:51.480 --> 27:53.767
- Carter!
- I need to talk to you right now!

27:55.240 --> 27:56.765
I'm gonna use the door.

27:56.840 --> 27:58.444
I am so sorry.

27:58.520 --> 28:01.524
Please excuse me for one minute.
I'm gonna be right back.

28:01.600 --> 28:03.568
Okay, how about we take
50 deep breaths.

28:03.640 --> 28:06.246
One hundred deep breaths. Okay?
I'll be right back.

28:06.320 --> 28:07.606
They were on the breakfast bar.

28:07.680 --> 28:09.364
- On the breakfast table?
- Yes!

28:09.440 --> 28:11.807
- That is insane!
- I know.

28:12.760 --> 28:14.762
Are you sure
that's what they were doing?

28:15.600 --> 28:17.170
I saw my dad's butt.

28:18.520 --> 28:20.887
- How?
- it was moving.

28:20.960 --> 28:24.282
Look, she'd never been there before.
He had to give her directions.

28:24.360 --> 28:25.691
They talked on the phone,

28:25.760 --> 28:29.401
or texted or sexted.
Or some disgusting thing.

28:29.520 --> 28:33.491
They planned this. it was planned.
They planned this.

28:36.120 --> 28:38.964
Wow, that must have been
some make-up sex.

28:41.840 --> 28:44.411
TREY: So these are all your uncles?
KIEKO: I have three.

28:44.480 --> 28:48.201
So we'll put Yoshi, Nakata,
and Paul at this table.

28:48.280 --> 28:50.851
KIEKO: Um, Yoshi's in jail.
TREY: Seriously?

28:50.920 --> 28:52.684
KIEKO: Or maybe he's out.
We don't keep in touch.

28:52.760 --> 28:54.091
TREY: We should find out,
so we don't offend anyone.

28:54.160 --> 28:55.161
I know, but...

28:56.280 --> 28:58.282
TREY: Do we have to invite him?
KIEKO: Um, no.

28:59.000 --> 29:00.365
Oh, hey, you're up.

29:00.440 --> 29:01.930
What's going on?

29:02.000 --> 29:05.004
We're mocking up seating charts
for the reception.

29:05.080 --> 29:07.162
Okay, so, originally,

29:07.240 --> 29:09.481
we had thought we would
have Mom's table over here,

29:09.600 --> 29:13.400
and Dad's table way over here, and then
this is three generations of Kobayashis.

29:13.520 --> 29:16.091
Yellow was the only other
color we had.

29:16.160 --> 29:17.525
Yeah, I just thought...

29:17.600 --> 29:19.762
(LAUGHING)
What are the odds?

29:19.840 --> 29:23.242
But thanks to your handiwork,
we had thought maybe

29:23.320 --> 29:27.325
we could have Mom and Dad's tables,
next to each other or...

29:27.440 --> 29:28.771
A family table?

29:28.840 --> 29:30.569
My parents and your
parents all sit together?

29:30.640 --> 29:31.801
No.

29:31.880 --> 29:34.121
Well, no, it's okay.
We're gonna do a dry run first,

29:34.200 --> 29:36.646
because her parents want to meet Mom
and Dad before the wedding anyway.

29:36.720 --> 29:38.290
- No.
- I mean, it won't be a big deal.

29:38.360 --> 29:41.125
Not a big dinner.
Just tea or something.

29:41.200 --> 29:43.521
No, no, look, Mom and Dad
should go here and here,

29:43.600 --> 29:46.126
and they are not to interact
in any capacity at any time.

29:46.200 --> 29:48.202
Do you understand?

29:49.720 --> 29:52.166
Okay, look, Lauren and
I will go to tea, okay?

29:52.240 --> 29:53.287
She likes tea.

29:53.360 --> 29:55.966
She likes weird tea, like rooibos and
oolong and all that bullshit, okay?

29:56.040 --> 29:58.008
- It'll be awesome.
- All right, I mean...

29:58.080 --> 29:59.081
(DOOR BUZZING)

29:59.240 --> 30:00.651
Oh, that's Gary.

30:01.200 --> 30:02.486
Wait. What?

30:02.560 --> 30:04.847
Yeah, he called earlier saying
he needed to talk to me and you.

30:04.920 --> 30:05.967
I told him to swing by.

30:06.040 --> 30:08.361
Oh, no, no, no. No, don't let him up.
We're not here.

30:08.440 --> 30:09.441
I just let him up.

30:09.520 --> 30:10.851
No, no, no,
but don't buzz him up.

30:10.920 --> 30:12.763
There's not an unbuzz button.

30:13.800 --> 30:15.006
(DOOR OPENS AND SHUTS)

30:15.080 --> 30:16.081
TREY:
Hey, what up, G?

30:16.240 --> 30:19.289
What's up, T?

30:19.360 --> 30:20.361
When did that start?

30:20.440 --> 30:23.330
It's recent, but it makes me
feel like I'm in my 50s.

30:23.400 --> 30:25.004
- Can I sit?
- Actually, I have to step out.

30:25.080 --> 30:27.048
GARY: Chill, Carter.
This will just take a second.

30:27.120 --> 30:29.771
Kieko, do you mind
if I talk to the boys alone?

30:29.840 --> 30:31.763
Yeah, of course.

30:34.920 --> 30:36.729
I'm not very good
at this stuff,

30:36.800 --> 30:40.247
but it's important and
a little awkward.

30:41.400 --> 30:42.731
You guys mean
a lot to me.

30:42.800 --> 30:43.961
You're my family.

30:44.400 --> 30:46.164
Okay, look,
Trey doesn't know, okay?

30:46.280 --> 30:47.361
He doesn't know.

30:47.440 --> 30:50.205
- What are you talking about?
- Shh.

30:50.280 --> 30:52.681
I just want to be a part of this.

30:52.760 --> 30:56.606
So consider it an
anonymous donation.

30:57.080 --> 31:01.449
This should take care of the reception
and maybe some top-shelf liquor.

31:01.520 --> 31:03.045
G does not drink rail.

31:03.760 --> 31:04.807
Wow.

31:04.880 --> 31:08.123
Okay, look, Gary, no.

31:09.280 --> 31:10.611
- No?
- No?

31:10.720 --> 31:13.041
Look, what I mean to say is,
it's very nice of you, Gary,

31:13.120 --> 31:15.248
but it's just not the right time.

31:15.320 --> 31:16.367
- Yes, it is.
- Well...

31:16.440 --> 31:17.646
- Well, sure it is.
- Okay.

31:17.720 --> 31:21.042
Look, I know
you want to do it all on your own.

31:21.120 --> 31:23.726
Your mom used
the word "commandeered."

