How in the world is he supposed
to have any faith whatsoever

46:24.640 --> 46:26.961
in the whole stupid
idea of marriage,

46:27.040 --> 46:29.361
if you two just keep
making a joke out of it?

46:29.440 --> 46:30.646
Stop it right there.

46:30.720 --> 46:32.961
You've never been married,
and you've never been divorced,

46:33.040 --> 46:35.281
so you do not know
what commitment is.

46:35.360 --> 46:36.361
You don't know.

46:36.480 --> 46:39.051
The most in love I've ever seen you
is with that mangy little dog you had.

46:39.120 --> 46:40.690
- Don't, don't...
- You keep Blackie out of this.

46:40.760 --> 46:42.330
No, I was right there,
Carter.

46:42.400 --> 46:44.004
- All right, all right.
- You weren't there.

46:44.080 --> 46:46.731
Are you gonna let him talk
to me this way?

46:46.800 --> 46:48.131
- (BOTH ARGUING)
- Shh. Quiet. Be quiet.

46:48.240 --> 46:50.925
We're in a Japanese restaurant.
Stop it, please.

46:53.240 --> 46:57.006
Now you get your ass back inside
and you apologize to the Takahashis.

46:58.560 --> 46:59.686
I'm...

46:59.760 --> 47:02.240
Come on. Come on.

47:02.840 --> 47:04.444
It's Kobayashis.

47:07.400 --> 47:09.050
You can just never
stop parenting.

47:09.120 --> 47:10.326
I know.

47:10.400 --> 47:12.767
Yeah, can't let it go.

47:12.840 --> 47:14.080
You were great.

47:17.400 --> 47:18.925
- Do we have to go back?
- No, no, come on.

47:19.000 --> 47:20.331
Okay, good.

47:27.040 --> 47:28.166
Carter.

47:28.280 --> 47:30.089
What a nice surprise.

47:33.880 --> 47:35.325
What's up, "C"?

47:35.720 --> 47:38.564
Gary, where does Mom keep all that
stuff that she never throws out,

47:38.640 --> 47:42.406
the pictures and the letters and
all the lawsuits and legal stuff?

47:42.480 --> 47:45.086
In the garage.
Hope you have a few days.

47:45.160 --> 47:46.525
Awesome.

47:47.760 --> 47:48.841
What the...

48:18.760 --> 48:22.685
Hey, I don't know if you heard the
news, but Trey is getting married.

48:22.760 --> 48:25.843
And, well, Elka,

48:25.920 --> 48:30.164
I had this really cool, really fun idea
that I thought you would love.

48:33.080 --> 48:36.084
I'm gonna call you back.

48:37.480 --> 48:38.720
Elka?

48:38.800 --> 48:41.041
- Yes.
- I didn't know you still talked.

48:41.120 --> 48:43.851
We don't.
I just had this idea that

48:43.920 --> 48:47.481
maybe if my dad were to bump
into Elka even for a second,

48:47.560 --> 48:50.404
he would get that look in his eye,
the panther,

48:50.480 --> 48:52.164
and my mom would be
an afterthought.

48:52.680 --> 48:55.365
Wow, panther.

48:56.720 --> 48:58.927
Um, I really think you need
to take a step back.

48:59.040 --> 49:00.041
What do you mean?

49:00.120 --> 49:02.805
They're adults.
Let them handle it.

49:02.880 --> 49:05.281
Oh, no, no, no, see?
I'm the adult. Okay?

49:05.360 --> 49:08.170
And, once again, I need to
remind them that they do not,

49:08.240 --> 49:10.322
under any circumstances,
belong together.

49:10.400 --> 49:14.564
Them together is
bad for everyone.

49:14.680 --> 49:16.045
Especially me.

49:16.840 --> 49:20.731
Makes sense. I mean, how could
Rick turn out any other way?

49:21.160 --> 49:22.127
What?

49:22.200 --> 49:25.807
It was in the book,
the one that you lied about.

49:25.880 --> 49:28.451
Dr. Judith came by.
She had some questions for me.

49:28.520 --> 49:30.727
She had a lot of questions.

49:30.800 --> 49:32.290
You gotta be kidding me.

49:32.360 --> 49:36.524
How come you can't tell me
about this, about any of it?

49:38.560 --> 49:42.167
Because I just...

49:43.360 --> 49:45.203
I can't believe she would
go behind my back.

49:45.280 --> 49:48.170
I mean, do you know that
she's not an actual doctor?

49:48.240 --> 49:49.765
- That she just does research?
- Right.

49:49.880 --> 49:50.961
Like, as a job?

49:51.040 --> 49:55.284
She just digs and digs
and digs and...

50:00.640 --> 50:02.722
I know it's a weird way
to wear a hat,

50:02.800 --> 50:04.928
but it just feels comfortable.

50:05.000 --> 50:06.843
She told me she wants me
to wear a wedding ring,

50:06.920 --> 50:10.083
but I said the only ring
I wear goes in my eyebrow.

50:10.160 --> 50:12.640
What does this have
to do with anything?

50:12.760 --> 50:14.171
(DOOR OPENS)

50:16.280 --> 50:19.443
Carter. I don't have
you on my schedule.

50:19.520 --> 50:22.649
Yeah, well, I figured, once you started
snooping around behind my back,

50:22.720 --> 50:24.370
all formalities were off.

50:24.440 --> 50:26.090
I can see you're very upset.

50:26.160 --> 50:27.605
What, are you a therapist now?

50:27.680 --> 50:30.251
Oh, and by the way,
don't let the new couch fool you

50:30.320 --> 50:31.845
or the new chair. What is it?

50:31.920 --> 50:33.285
It's a knockoff of
an Eames chair.

50:33.360 --> 50:35.522
That's not the point.
That's not why I was saying that.

50:35.600 --> 50:38.729
Oh, my God.
You're Rick.

50:40.560 --> 50:43.609
Mark a.k.a. Louis.

50:44.280 --> 50:47.602
Louis with the au pair
and the stutter.

50:47.680 --> 50:51.162
Stutter's gone.
I did marry the au pair.

50:52.120 --> 50:57.490
Can I just say, the birthday story,
such a heartbreaker.

50:58.040 --> 51:02.762
I mean, a seminal moment in my life,
and it's not even my life.

51:02.840 --> 51:04.080
Okay, Mark.

51:04.160 --> 51:05.491
Oh, all right.

51:05.560 --> 51:08.609
Could you just give
us a moment, okay?

51:08.680 --> 51:11.160
You, outside. Stay.

51:11.240 --> 51:12.241
Copy that.

51:15.240 --> 51:17.208
Is this about Lauren?

51:17.320 --> 51:21.041
- Yeah.
- Yeah? Okay. Well, sorry.

51:21.120 --> 51:22.770
I was just trying to
get a full picture.

51:22.840 --> 51:24.683
- No, it's fine.
- Really?

51:24.760 --> 51:26.364
Thing is you're barking
up the wrong tree.

51:26.440 --> 51:29.125
If I were you,
I would go to the source.

51:29.840 --> 51:31.001
I would talk to my parents.

51:31.080 --> 51:32.445
- Really?
- Yes.

51:32.520 --> 51:34.363
Pound them with questions,
really dig.

51:35.160 --> 51:36.321
See this box?

51:36.400 --> 51:38.050
This will help you.

51:38.120 --> 51:40.487
It's pictures, letters,
legal documents.

51:40.560 --> 51:42.801
You should show it to them
and ask them all about it.

51:42.880 --> 51:44.962
Okay, thank you,
and I will do that.

51:45.080 --> 51:46.320
Okay?

51:46.400 --> 51:48.767
Before the weekend.

51:48.840 --> 51:50.126
Got it.

51:51.680 --> 51:53.967
Hey, Lauren's really nice.

51:54.040 --> 51:56.441
You've been keeping a lot of
secrets from her, though, huh?

51:56.520 --> 51:58.443
Who does that remind you of?

51:58.520 --> 52:00.966
You are incredibly unprofessional.

52:04.320 --> 52:05.685
Get on it.

52:21.680 --> 52:22.681
- Trivia night.
- Trivia night?

52:22.760 --> 52:23.807
- Trivia night.
- What's that?

52:23.880 --> 52:25.291
Hey.

52:26.760 --> 52:28.171
Hey.
Hey.

52:28.640 --> 52:30.005
Do you work here?

52:30.080 --> 52:31.605
Kind of. It's my place.

52:33.560 --> 52:35.403
I'm sorry. I'm Carter.

52:36.080 --> 52:38.526
- Charles.
- Charles.

52:38.600 --> 52:41.080
So how do you two know each other?

52:42.800 --> 52:44.962
Well, we're part of a...

52:45.040 --> 52:46.007
- Book club.
- Book club.

52:46.080 --> 52:48.845
We're in a book club together.

52:48.920 --> 52:54.051
That's right. We're just finishing
<i>The Importance of Being Earnest.</i>

52:54.120 --> 52:55.121
That's a play.

52:55.640 --> 52:57.244
It's a progressive book club.

52:58.480 --> 52:59.811
(LAUGHING)

53:00.440 --> 53:02.966
All right, well, check's paid.
You want to go?

53:04.280 --> 53:05.964
Um,

53:06.040 --> 53:09.647
actually, you know what?
I think I'm gonna stay here

53:09.720 --> 53:12.644
and chat with Carter because

53:13.880 --> 53:18.283
there's a few things about
the play that I didn't quite get.

53:18.600 --> 53:19.601
Hmm.

53:19.680 --> 53:21.569
That's a farce.

53:21.640 --> 53:24.564
They farced the moral disintegration
of Victorian England.

53:25.800 --> 53:27.484
I didn't actually read it.

53:27.600 --> 53:29.364
I'll call you later.

53:29.440 --> 53:30.805
All right.

53:31.720 --> 53:33.609
- Nice meeting you.
- You, too.

53:33.680 --> 53:35.444
- Thanks.
- Oh, you're welcome.

53:35.520 --> 53:36.681
Sorry.

53:40.800 --> 53:42.290
That was my ex-husband.

53:42.720 --> 53:45.769
That was your ex-husband.
Ol' Man River?

53:46.160 --> 53:48.162
I actually think
he's quite sexy.

53:48.320 --> 53:51.164
(STAMMERING)
I do, too. I was just...

53:51.680 --> 53:58.529
So if you own the place,
then the wine's free?

53:59.840 --> 54:00.841
Yeah.

54:01.840 --> 54:05.447
CARTER: That lake house
was everything when I was a kid.

54:05.520 --> 54:09.047
The drive up there,
the smell of the lake.

54:09.160 --> 54:14.803
We had this bell,
this rusty, super loud bell.

54:14.880 --> 54:16.291
It was from a ship
or something.

54:16.360 --> 54:19.648
We could only ring it
when we first arrived.

54:20.240 --> 54:21.241
Um...

54:21.920 --> 54:25.527
It was just kind of awesome.
I don't know.

54:28.280 --> 54:31.489
Never been back.
Not since my ninth birthday.

54:34.680 --> 54:40.403
My parents sort of sucked
the joy right out of it, you know?

54:40.480 --> 54:42.721
- Fuck them.
- Yeah.

54:45.200 --> 54:48.807
How old were you
when you got married?

54:48.880 --> 54:50.211
Nineteen.

54:51.760 --> 54:53.808
It only lasted three years.

54:55.040 --> 54:57.486
But I got engaged twice after that.

54:58.080 --> 55:01.721
Wait a second. I just figured out
who you are in the book.

55:02.760 --> 55:03.807
You're Claire.

55:04.840 --> 55:07.241
Had her first boyfriend
when she was nine.

55:07.320 --> 55:10.688
You are Claire. Right?

55:10.760 --> 55:15.721
I have two dogs that need to
go out, so I'm gonna go.

55:16.560 --> 55:19.040
Okay. Yeah. Sure.

55:19.120 --> 55:20.690
All right.

55:20.760 --> 55:22.000
Thanks. This was...

55:22.080 --> 55:26.768
Oh, no, thank you.
it was nice talking to you.

55:26.840 --> 55:28.968
- Yeah. You, too.
- All right.

55:29.080 --> 55:30.081
- Cool.
- Yep.

55:31.680 --> 55:32.806
- Ow!
- Careful, careful.

55:33.760 --> 55:35.569
(DISHES CLATTERING)

55:51.560 --> 55:52.721
Hey, Etta.

55:53.440 --> 55:55.442
I forgot my purse.

56:06.400 --> 56:08.846
Maybe this isn't such
a good idea.

56:15.080 --> 56:16.047
Those look so good.

56:16.120 --> 56:17.565
Oh, no, no, don't.

56:17.640 --> 56:18.880
Don't you dare.

56:18.960 --> 56:20.246
All right.
I'll have it.

56:20.960 --> 56:23.008
Oh. Okay. Okay.

56:23.640 --> 56:26.962
Three, one, four, and two.

56:27.040 --> 56:30.169
I totally agree.
I'm so excited!

56:34.400 --> 56:36.323
Hey, what do you think?

56:37.160 --> 56:38.207
What?

56:38.280 --> 56:40.089
About the cake.
What's your pick?

56:40.160 --> 56:43.369
Oh, God, it's such
a tough choice. Um...

56:45.320 --> 56:48.688
They all taste the same,
and no one will like them.

56:48.800 --> 56:52.088
I don't get you, man.

56:53.680 --> 56:56.968
Look, if you're against this wedding,
you just need to come out and say that.

56:57.040 --> 56:58.087
I'm not.

56:58.160 --> 56:59.844
Well, then what is it?

57:00.440 --> 57:03.569
Things are just kind of out
of control right now, okay?

57:05.440 --> 57:06.646
I don't know
what that means.

57:06.720 --> 57:08.802
Well, it means
that you don't want to know, okay?

57:08.880 --> 57:10.291
So don't worry about it.

57:10.360 --> 57:12.488
You can tell me.
I'm a grown man, Carter.

57:14.520 --> 57:17.126
- Mom and Dad are together.
- What?

57:17.200 --> 57:19.202
That's right. I may have accidentally
gotten them back together.

57:19.280 --> 57:20.281
So there you go.

57:20.360 --> 57:22.362
- Together, together?
- Yeah.

57:26.480 --> 57:28.562
- Shit.
- Yeah.

57:29.480 --> 57:31.164
What do we do about this?
What should we do?

57:31.240 --> 57:32.605
I don't know.
I'm out of ideas.

57:32.680 --> 57:34.808
So why don't you
take the reins, okay?

57:35.600 --> 57:37.489
I got my own problems.

57:38.920 --> 57:40.570
(SIREN CHIRPING)

57:53.320 --> 57:56.324
They're saying multiple code violations
and not having a proper lease filed.

57:56.400 --> 57:57.925
(WHISPERS) What the fuck?

57:58.880 --> 57:59.881
Jesus.

58:00.480 --> 58:02.164
You're out. One week.

58:02.240 --> 58:03.207
What?

58:03.280 --> 58:05.408
Your mother?
That's just sad.

58:05.480 --> 58:08.324
Okay, Sondra,

58:08.400 --> 58:11.404
I know that you're upset,
and I actually don't blame you,

58:11.480 --> 58:13.801
but I don't think we should
do anything rash here.

58:13.880 --> 58:17.123
(STAMMERING) I mean,
both of you, you're just...

58:17.200 --> 58:18.929
You're so terrific together.

58:19.000 --> 58:20.809
Are you fucking serious, Carter?

58:20.880 --> 58:23.167
You've hated me from day one.
You call me the Cuntessa.

58:23.240 --> 58:27.165
I don't think I called you that.
That's terrible. I hate that.

58:27.240 --> 58:29.686
Excuse me, will you be careful
with that? It's very valuable.

58:29.760 --> 58:31.364
Sondra, let me buy
you out, please.

58:31.440 --> 58:34.489
Okay? I can get money.
I can get a loan of some sort,

58:34.560 --> 58:37.131
and I can't kick all
these people to the street.

58:37.240 --> 58:39.208
- Okay.
- Okay? Really?

58:39.280 --> 58:40.327
Yes.

58:42.600 --> 58:44.489
- Great.
- $100 million.

58:45.840 --> 58:46.841
Fine. $50.

58:46.960 --> 58:48.007
Okay, um...

58:48.080 --> 58:50.048
Do you know how many men
I could have married?

58:50.120 --> 58:52.282
A lot of men.

58:52.360 --> 58:53.361
And I married your father,

58:53.440 --> 58:55.886
who had an adult son
the same age as me.

58:55.960 --> 58:57.121
I'm a year younger than you.

58:57.200 --> 58:58.326
- You think?
- Yeah.

58:58.400 --> 58:59.401
Congratulations.

58:59.480 --> 59:00.481
It's irrelevant.

59:01.440 --> 59:04.842
You didn't spend five minutes
getting to know who I was.

59:04.920 --> 59:07.651
You just treated me
like some unwelcomed guest.

59:08.920 --> 59:09.967
Wow.

59:12.440 --> 59:15.649
Maybe in another time
we would have been friends.

59:16.800 --> 59:18.006
No.

59:18.640 --> 59:20.369
You have a week
to get out of here.

59:20.440 --> 59:22.044
You know what, Sondra?

59:22.160 --> 59:23.321
You...

59:37.160 --> 59:41.085
I'm dying here, man.
You got to move those accounts now.

59:41.160 --> 59:44.528
I don't know.
The Caymans? Delaware?

59:44.680 --> 59:47.126
Yeah, Delaware, I saw a thing
on the Internet about it.

59:47.200 --> 59:49.851
I'll call you back.
Numbnuts is here.

59:53.040 --> 59:55.327
You dumb son of a bitch.

59:55.400 --> 59:58.006
You dumb, dumb,
dumb son of a bitch.

59:58.080 --> 01:00:01.209
I mean, there's a reason we used you
as a go-between all these years.

01:00:01.680 --> 01:00:03.125
Your brother sucks at it.

01:00:03.200 --> 01:00:05.009
- He told her?
- No, he e-mailed me to see

01:00:05.120 --> 01:00:09.523
if what you said was true to an
account that I share with Sondra.

01:00:09.600 --> 01:00:12.001
Okay, well, I wouldn't
have done that.

01:00:13.680 --> 01:00:16.160
You don't end a marriage
like this, son.

01:00:18.240 --> 01:00:20.481
I could have made her miserable.

01:00:20.560 --> 01:00:22.722
I could have gotten
her to leave me.

01:00:22.840 --> 01:00:24.729
Do you have any idea
how much cheaper that is?

01:00:25.280 --> 01:00:26.884
Guess who's here.

01:00:29.400 --> 01:00:33.007
We were hoping to hold all this off
until after Trey's big day.

01:00:33.080 --> 01:00:36.482
Darling, you know Daddy and I
did not want it to go this way.

01:00:36.560 --> 01:00:39.040
You told me it was okay
to plan my wedding.

01:00:39.120 --> 01:00:40.849
I thought it was.

01:00:40.920 --> 01:00:42.524
Well, Kieko is pissed.

01:00:42.600 --> 01:00:44.364
She wants to postpone.

01:00:44.440 --> 01:00:45.965
The guest list is blown to shit.

01:00:46.040 --> 01:00:47.371
Sandra's really pissed.

01:00:47.440 --> 01:00:50.125
Yeah, and I already sent Gary's
money to that DJ in Tel Aviv.

01:00:50.200 --> 01:00:51.531
You think those guys give refunds?

01:00:52.360 --> 01:00:55.170
Listen, Carter, you knew about this
the whole time.

01:00:55.240 --> 01:00:56.287
Why didn't you just tell me?

01:00:56.360 --> 01:00:58.044
Because I was trying
to protect you.

01:00:58.120 --> 01:00:59.645
Well, since when is
that your job?

01:00:59.760 --> 01:01:01.171
- Since when is it my job?
- Yeah.

01:01:01.240 --> 01:01:02.890
Since always.

01:01:02.960 --> 01:01:04.121
Trey, let me tell you something.

01:01:04.200 --> 01:01:07.727
The reason you're so clear-headed
about getting married

01:01:07.800 --> 01:01:12.567
is because I shielded you
from these two your whole life,

01:01:12.640 --> 01:01:14.449
which, by the way,
almost didn't happen.

01:01:14.520 --> 01:01:18.525
That's right. You were a last-ditch
effort to save this marriage.

01:01:19.400 --> 01:01:20.731
I mean, you're not even a person.

01:01:20.800 --> 01:01:22.245
You're a Hail Mary.

01:01:22.320 --> 01:01:23.765
That's a stupid lie.

01:01:23.840 --> 01:01:25.171
Darling, you were an accident.

01:01:26.440 --> 01:01:28.681
Carter, you couldn't have timed this
any worse.

01:01:28.760 --> 01:01:30.569
Yeah, I agree.
I think he's jealous.

01:01:30.640 --> 01:01:31.641
Jealous?

01:01:32.080 --> 01:01:33.525
Kieko thinks you're jealous.

01:01:33.600 --> 01:01:35.011
How long have you been
going with Lauren?

01:01:35.080 --> 01:01:36.605
Oh, since the beginning of time.

01:01:36.680 --> 01:01:38.682
- Exactly. We're in the game.
- And he's on the sidelines.

01:01:38.760 --> 01:01:40.250
- Yeah.
- No, wait a second.

01:01:40.320 --> 01:01:42.004
- I'm in the game.
- Carter, you have to stop

01:01:42.080 --> 01:01:43.809
pissing on our love parade.

01:01:44.760 --> 01:01:47.650
I can't... I don't even...

01:01:48.280 --> 01:01:49.327
You know what?

01:01:49.400 --> 01:01:53.610
You people, I want all of
you out of my garage.

01:01:57.440 --> 01:01:59.488
(GARAGE DOOR LIFTING)

01:02:00.560 --> 01:02:02.324
I quit this family.

01:02:15.240 --> 01:02:17.163
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

01:02:17.560 --> 01:02:19.324
Ah, fuck you.

01:03:02.040 --> 01:03:03.883
(GIGGLING) They can't.

01:03:15.320 --> 01:03:16.765
(DOOR BUZZING)

01:03:17.120 --> 01:03:18.485
(MOUTHING)

01:03:45.160 --> 01:03:46.161
(APPLAUSE)

01:03:46.240 --> 01:03:48.607
MR. STRINGER: Needless to say,
I kept that ticket stub.

01:03:48.720 --> 01:03:49.767
(LAUGHTER)

01:03:49.840 --> 01:03:52.923
And so, 37 years later,
here we are,

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:56.766
surrounded by our dearest friends
and best of all, our children.

01:03:57.840 --> 01:04:00.605
Cynthia and her incredible
husband David,

01:04:01.160 --> 01:04:03.640
Tyler and the beautiful Maureen,

01:04:03.720 --> 01:04:06.929
Lauren and Carter.

01:04:08.480 --> 01:04:11.211
And, Kate, because of you,
I fear nothing.

01:04:11.280 --> 01:04:13.009
- Sweetie.
- Thank you.

01:04:13.440 --> 01:04:14.680
ALL: Awww.

01:04:14.760 --> 01:04:15.921
- Thank you all.
- (APPLAUSE)

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:17.365
(GLASS CLINKING)

01:04:18.440 --> 01:04:20.090
Hey. Sorry.

01:04:20.160 --> 01:04:22.640
That was a little louder
than I thought.

01:04:22.720 --> 01:04:23.767
Hey, everybody.

01:04:24.640 --> 01:04:26.290
Steve, that was a
great speech.

01:04:26.360 --> 01:04:27.885
That was really nice.

01:04:27.960 --> 01:04:33.000
And I've been to several of these now,
your anniversary parties,

01:04:33.080 --> 01:04:37.722
and, um, I never quite
honestly appreciated them.

01:04:37.800 --> 01:04:42.488
I guess I always just sort of
looked forward to the food,

01:04:43.120 --> 01:04:46.602
and I have something to
share with you.

01:04:46.680 --> 01:04:50.924
And it's sort of...

01:04:51.000 --> 01:04:52.126
Carter, you shouldn't have.

01:04:52.240 --> 01:04:54.971
Oh, well, I didn't,
Mr. Stringer.

01:04:55.120 --> 01:04:58.010
This is actually for Lauren.

01:05:00.400 --> 01:05:02.607
Um, maybe later?

01:05:02.680 --> 01:05:07.049
No, I think right now
is a good time.

01:05:07.480 --> 01:05:08.561
Okay.

01:05:08.640 --> 01:05:10.005
Excuse me.

01:05:11.800 --> 01:05:12.881
What is it?

01:05:12.960 --> 01:05:14.291
I'm not gonna tell you.

01:05:14.360 --> 01:05:16.169
That's kind of the point, right?

01:05:20.360 --> 01:05:21.407
Excuse me.

01:05:21.520 --> 01:05:22.646
Sorry.

01:05:28.880 --> 01:05:29.961
Oh, wow.

01:05:33.480 --> 01:05:34.447
(GUESTS EXCLAIM)

01:05:34.520 --> 01:05:35.726
(GASPS)

01:05:38.680 --> 01:05:40.205
How about we make it official?

01:05:40.320 --> 01:05:41.765
ALL: Ohhh.
(LAUGHTER)

01:05:41.840 --> 01:05:43.080
More champagne!

01:05:43.200 --> 01:05:44.281
(APPLAUSE)

01:05:44.360 --> 01:05:46.328
I think it's about time.

01:05:46.480 --> 01:05:47.811
(SCOFFS)

01:05:52.240 --> 01:05:53.480
Hey.

01:05:56.400 --> 01:05:59.688
I feel like you should be
slightly more elated.

01:05:59.760 --> 01:06:04.129
That was the most public display
of personal crisis I've ever seen.

01:06:04.200 --> 01:06:06.043
What?

01:06:06.120 --> 01:06:08.168
What are you
trying to prove?

01:06:08.240 --> 01:06:10.686
I'm not trying to
prove anything.

01:06:13.560 --> 01:06:17.201
Just looking for some,
I don't know, some stability.

01:06:17.280 --> 01:06:19.521
Marriage is not stability.

01:06:19.600 --> 01:06:21.568
Stability is stability.

01:06:21.640 --> 01:06:22.880
What are you talking about?

01:06:24.800 --> 01:06:27.565
Look at the people in
that room, Lauren.

01:06:28.600 --> 01:06:30.284
What do they have
to do with me?

01:06:30.360 --> 01:06:32.044
- I'm not them.
- Well...

01:06:32.120 --> 01:06:33.963
I don't even know
where this is coming from.

01:06:34.040 --> 01:06:35.326
I mean, why now?

01:06:35.400 --> 01:06:37.129
We're not in a good place.

01:06:37.200 --> 01:06:39.168
We are in a weird place.

01:06:39.240 --> 01:06:41.288
No, that's all done.

01:06:41.360 --> 01:06:43.169
I worked through
all that, and I'm...

01:06:43.240 --> 01:06:44.685
Carter,

01:06:45.920 --> 01:06:47.684
you didn't even ask
me to marry you.

01:06:47.760 --> 01:06:49.649
You said,

01:06:49.720 --> 01:06:51.927
"Let's make it official."

01:06:53.480 --> 01:06:55.562
Let's not. Not now.

01:07:00.200 --> 01:07:01.406
Are you...

01:07:21.280 --> 01:07:23.123
(METALLIC CLATTERING)

01:07:27.640 --> 01:07:30.041
JUDITH: You skipped
your last two appointments.

01:07:30.560 --> 01:07:32.722
You aren't returning my calls.

01:07:32.800 --> 01:07:34.643
What's up?

01:07:35.320 --> 01:07:37.322
Uh, I'm avoiding you.

01:07:37.400 --> 01:07:38.731
But why?

01:07:39.480 --> 01:07:41.562
We're just getting started.

01:07:41.640 --> 01:07:43.529
No, you're just getting started.

01:07:43.600 --> 01:07:45.125
I'm done.

01:07:45.200 --> 01:07:47.089
I just got a six-figure advance.

01:07:47.160 --> 01:07:49.049
They don't give those things out
for nothing.

01:07:49.120 --> 01:07:50.326
We have something real here.

01:07:50.400 --> 01:07:52.289
Yeah, it's called my life.

01:07:52.360 --> 01:07:55.250
And I want you
to stop messing with it, okay?

01:07:55.320 --> 01:07:56.845
I'm not a fucking lab rat.

01:07:56.920 --> 01:07:59.571
Millions of people have
been helped by my research.

01:07:59.640 --> 01:08:02.689
And my next book
will help millions more.

01:08:02.760 --> 01:08:04.410
Okay, you were
supposed to help me.

01:08:04.480 --> 01:08:06.767
I know. I tried.
I tried to do both, and I couldn't.

01:08:06.840 --> 01:08:09.207
But, Carter, when you walked
into my office that first day,

01:08:09.280 --> 01:08:13.080
everything about you
just screamed possibility.

01:08:13.600 --> 01:08:15.409
But you said I
was so together.

01:08:15.480 --> 01:08:17.130
Well, I had to say that.

01:08:17.200 --> 01:08:20.090
A scientist only gets an opportunity
like this once in a lifetime.

01:08:20.200 --> 01:08:21.361
I'm a scientist. You're data.

01:08:22.319 --> 01:08:24.607
You were so sure.

01:08:24.680 --> 01:08:27.286
You were so confident
that you had escaped the chaos

01:08:27.359 --> 01:08:29.249
of your childhood.

01:08:29.319 --> 01:08:32.846
But you're growing now,
and growth is painful.

01:08:33.520 --> 01:08:35.045
You're welcome.

01:08:36.520 --> 01:08:38.045
What kind of a doctor are you?

01:08:38.960 --> 01:08:40.121
(CHUCKLES)

01:08:40.200 --> 01:08:42.362
I brought this back for you.
Take a look at it.

01:08:42.880 --> 01:08:44.529
It explains so much.

01:08:44.640 --> 01:08:45.687
Not about your parents.

01:08:46.760 --> 01:08:48.569
Hey, you want to quit, Carter?
Go ahead.

01:08:48.640 --> 01:08:51.962
But sooner or later,
you're gonna have to deal.

01:09:33.640 --> 01:09:35.051
(DOOR SHUTS)

01:10:25.600 --> 01:10:26.806
(CLANGS)

01:11:37.480 --> 01:11:38.606
Carter?

01:11:39.280 --> 01:11:40.406
Gary?

01:11:42.600 --> 01:11:44.250
What are you doing here?

01:11:45.720 --> 01:11:47.529
Your mother and I...

01:11:48.440 --> 01:11:50.249
We actually used to use the place.

01:11:51.240 --> 01:11:52.480
You did?

01:11:52.560 --> 01:11:55.211
Yeah. All the time.

01:11:55.280 --> 01:11:57.408
I repainted the canoe.

01:12:00.240 --> 01:12:01.287
Oh.

01:12:01.960 --> 01:12:06.249
I just thought I'd do some fishing.

01:12:06.320 --> 01:12:07.401
Clears my head.

01:12:08.120 --> 01:12:13.411
Look, Gary, I'm really sorry.

01:12:14.120 --> 01:12:17.442
Well, listen, my first two marriages
ended far worse.

01:12:19.480 --> 01:12:21.482
What are you doing here?

01:12:23.280 --> 01:12:24.884
Oh, I'm, uh...

01:12:29.040 --> 01:12:31.566
Just having an existential crisis.

01:12:31.720 --> 01:12:33.085
(GARY CHUCKLES)

01:12:35.440 --> 01:12:37.249
Want to come fishing?

01:12:38.120 --> 01:12:39.531
No. Thanks.

01:12:40.760 --> 01:12:42.000
Have fun.

01:12:59.920 --> 01:13:01.524
HUGH: I don't see him.

01:13:01.600 --> 01:13:03.568
Maybe he's in the water.

01:13:06.280 --> 01:13:07.691
Carter, what are you doing here?

01:13:08.640 --> 01:13:09.687
What are you doing here?

01:13:12.600 --> 01:13:15.410
TREY: Honey, it's all over the car.

01:13:15.480 --> 01:13:16.561
You don't smell it?

01:13:16.640 --> 01:13:18.927
I do, but I like it.

01:13:19.040 --> 01:13:21.930
It's all over the front of my pants.
It fell down.

01:13:23.440 --> 01:13:24.646
Who invited him?

01:13:24.720 --> 01:13:26.131
I don't know.
He's just here.

01:13:26.200 --> 01:13:27.725
Trey, get those ribs
in the fridge, please.

01:13:27.840 --> 01:13:28.921
TREY: Okay.

01:13:29.000 --> 01:13:31.128
Okay, what is going on?

01:13:31.200 --> 01:13:34.249
We're here for the night,
just kind of a family getaway.

01:13:34.320 --> 01:13:35.367
Oh.

01:13:35.440 --> 01:13:36.407
No offense.

01:13:36.480 --> 01:13:37.891
None taken.

01:13:37.960 --> 01:13:39.485
You quit us, remember?

01:13:39.600 --> 01:13:40.931
Darling, you need
some help with those?

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:43.480
No, no, I got 'em. I got 'em.

01:13:43.560 --> 01:13:45.608
Sweetie, put some of these
on a plate with some bread,

01:13:45.680 --> 01:13:46.920
and we'll get some
hors d'oeuvres going.

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:48.843
Bread and a plate.
Let's get this party started.

01:13:48.920 --> 01:13:51.127
Carter, hope you're hungry.

01:13:51.200 --> 01:13:52.725
MELISSA: Gary?

01:13:53.120 --> 01:13:54.201
What the hell is he doing here?

01:13:54.280 --> 01:13:55.441
They've been coming for years.

01:13:55.520 --> 01:13:58.171
- They what?
- No, no.

01:13:58.240 --> 01:14:00.368
Maybe once or twice.

01:14:00.440 --> 01:14:01.441
A month.

01:14:01.520 --> 01:14:03.966
On the ride up here, you said
you barely remember the place.

01:14:04.040 --> 01:14:06.361
Yeah, I barely remember
the place with you.

01:14:06.440 --> 01:14:07.965
You Google-mapped directions.

01:14:08.040 --> 01:14:09.371
I should probably go.

01:14:10.560 --> 01:14:12.005
SONDRA: I knew it.

01:14:12.400 --> 01:14:15.404
The security company called
and said the alarm had been tripped.

01:14:16.120 --> 01:14:17.281
Is she speaking to us?

01:14:17.800 --> 01:14:18.801
No.

01:14:18.880 --> 01:14:20.450
I'm sorry. There's an alarm?

01:14:20.560 --> 01:14:22.289
Yes, we added it a
couple months ago.

01:14:22.360 --> 01:14:23.964
HUGH:
It was her idea.

01:14:24.040 --> 01:14:25.963
What other improvements
has she made to my house?

01:14:26.040 --> 01:14:28.850
Well, Melissa, if you
actually need to know,

01:14:28.920 --> 01:14:33.164
we added a new septic system,
and I crocheted a few blankets.

01:14:33.280 --> 01:14:34.327
You crochet?

01:14:34.400 --> 01:14:36.448
Yes, asshole, I crochet.

01:14:37.800 --> 01:14:40.531
I also finished
all the puzzles in the house.

01:14:40.600 --> 01:14:43.604
Wait a second. Am I the only one
that hasn't been coming here?

01:14:43.680 --> 01:14:46.411
- We camped.
- But we never came in the house.

01:14:46.480 --> 01:14:47.720
Yeah, he made me pee
under the porch.

01:14:47.800 --> 01:14:48.926
You're welcome.

01:14:49.000 --> 01:14:50.764
SONDRA: Believe it or not,

01:14:50.880 --> 01:14:52.370
Hugh and I had
some happy memories here.

01:14:52.440 --> 01:14:53.930
And I had big plans for this place.

01:14:54.080 --> 01:14:55.081
Mmm-hmm.

01:14:55.200 --> 01:14:58.363
A third bedroom upstairs,
an outdoor shower...

01:14:59.080 --> 01:15:00.605
HUGH: Oh, boy.

01:15:02.120 --> 01:15:03.246
You'll never get this house.

01:15:03.320 --> 01:15:04.765
You haven't met my lawyer.

01:15:04.840 --> 01:15:07.525
Well, Hugh and I are very good at
tying it up in court, aren't we, Hugh?

01:15:07.600 --> 01:15:08.726
Oh, well, yeah.

01:15:08.800 --> 01:15:10.962
May I attempt to be a
voice of reason?

01:15:11.040 --> 01:15:12.690
Shut up, Gary.

01:15:12.760 --> 01:15:14.330
Don't tell Gary to shut up, please.

01:15:14.400 --> 01:15:15.731
- Dick.
- MELISSA: Gary!

01:15:15.800 --> 01:15:19.407
He is a dick. I had Carter out
of his restaurant in 12 hours.

01:15:19.480 --> 01:15:20.891
I'll have all of you
out of here in six.

01:15:20.917 --> 01:15:21.269
Great.

01:15:21.320 --> 01:15:22.526
What's up, Trey?

01:15:22.600 --> 01:15:23.601
Hey.

01:15:25.920 --> 01:15:27.763
Ah, this is fun.

01:15:33.400 --> 01:15:35.528
<i>Mom, how hard is it
to set up a guest room?</i>

01:15:36.960 --> 01:15:39.122
Can you put Daddy on the phone?

01:15:40.280 --> 01:15:42.442
Daddy, it's happening again.

01:15:43.960 --> 01:15:46.725
I don't know.
Just send me a plane ticket.

01:15:46.800 --> 01:15:48.609
Make sure it's an aisle seat.

01:15:53.640 --> 01:15:55.563
Look, I'm so sorry we
didn't invite you.

01:15:55.640 --> 01:15:56.801
- Oh, dude...
- I wanted to.

01:15:56.880 --> 01:15:58.848
Mom and Dad
would not let me invite you.

01:15:58.920 --> 01:16:00.968
- That's...
- He took my phone.

01:16:02.080 --> 01:16:04.242
- They're like fucking children.
- Yeah.

01:16:04.320 --> 01:16:06.322
I don't know how you've put up
with them all these years.

01:16:09.320 --> 01:16:12.210
Trey, I am sorry I messed up
your wedding.

01:16:12.280 --> 01:16:14.009
No. You didn't.

01:16:14.080 --> 01:16:15.491
No, no one did.

01:16:15.560 --> 01:16:18.166
It was just bad timing.

01:16:19.080 --> 01:16:20.570
Kieko thought that
you didn't like her,

01:16:20.680 --> 01:16:23.570
but then I showed her
that book that you're in,

01:16:23.680 --> 01:16:25.045
and now she does not care
what you think.

01:16:25.120 --> 01:16:26.121
(LAUGHS)

01:16:28.920 --> 01:16:30.160
- Do you smell something?
- (SNIFFING)

01:16:30.800 --> 01:16:33.167
Nature, man.
Let's look at it.

01:16:33.240 --> 01:16:34.366
Holy shit.

01:16:35.120 --> 01:16:36.690
What the hell?

01:16:42.280 --> 01:16:43.930
- Holy shit!
- Holy shit!

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:45.968
- Holy shit!
- Holy shit, holy shit!

01:16:46.240 --> 01:16:47.924
Water!
We need water!

01:16:48.040 --> 01:16:50.281
- Why? What's the matter?
- Kieko, call 611.

01:16:50.360 --> 01:16:51.850
Why? What's wrong?

01:16:51.960 --> 01:16:55.043
Tupperware bowls,
we need water.

01:16:55.120 --> 01:16:56.690
Guys, just shut up.

01:16:56.760 --> 01:16:58.000
There is a fire.

01:16:58.080 --> 01:16:59.206
And it is right outside.

01:16:59.280 --> 01:17:00.486
If you say "fire..."

01:17:00.560 --> 01:17:02.164
Why did you say "water"?

01:17:02.240 --> 01:17:03.810
- Are you serious?
- Fill it up.

01:17:04.920 --> 01:17:06.729
Oh, my God,
the house is on fire.

01:17:07.040 --> 01:17:08.724
I think Carter started it.

01:17:09.080 --> 01:17:10.366
(SCREAMS)

01:17:11.240 --> 01:17:12.480
Where's my purse?

01:17:21.880 --> 01:17:24.884
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

01:17:30.920 --> 01:17:33.241
FIRE CHIEF: All right, folks, there's
really nothing left to salvage.

01:17:33.320 --> 01:17:36.802
You got some canoes
and some fishing gear.

01:17:36.920 --> 01:17:40.049
So whose place is it?

01:17:40.120 --> 01:17:41.406
It's hers.

01:17:43.560 --> 01:17:47.531
Well, it's very big of you, Hugh,
but I got what I came for.

01:17:50.160 --> 01:17:51.605
I'll buy it.

01:17:52.400 --> 01:17:53.401
You'll what?

01:17:53.960 --> 01:17:55.644
I'll buy it as is.

01:17:58.080 --> 01:18:00.606
Sold.
Knock yourself out.

01:18:01.600 --> 01:18:03.090
Okay. Let's go.

01:18:03.160 --> 01:18:05.970
Bacon and eggs on Gary.
Come on.

01:18:06.040 --> 01:18:07.883
- Thanks, Gary.
- I'm kidding. Come on, Gary.

01:18:07.960 --> 01:18:10.167
GARY: I'll take the canoes
if nobody wants 'em.

01:18:10.240 --> 01:18:12.049
SONDRA: Go for it, Gary.
HUGH: 80 bucks for the pair.

01:18:12.120 --> 01:18:13.849
MELISSA: Lock up
on your way out, Carter.

01:18:13.920 --> 01:18:15.684
Still got the view.

01:18:21.560 --> 01:18:24.609
<i>JUDITH: Children of divorce
experience certain moments</i>

01:18:24.720 --> 01:18:29.362
<i>unique to them and ones
that they'll never forget.</i>

01:18:29.440 --> 01:18:33.126
<i>This is the very first generation
to grow up with divorce,</i>

01:18:33.200 --> 01:18:36.204
<i>not as the exception,
but as a fact of life</i>

01:18:36.280 --> 01:18:38.726
<i>for nearly every other
house on the block.</i>

01:18:38.800 --> 01:18:42.088
<i>They don't have healthy
relationship models to follow,</i>

01:18:42.160 --> 01:18:44.527
<i>just hard lessons in
whatnot to do.</i>

01:18:45.120 --> 01:18:50.684
<i>I believe these six people are the
brave pioneers of a brand-new world.</i>

01:18:51.240 --> 01:18:52.241
<i>Thank you.</i>

01:18:52.320 --> 01:18:53.321
(APPLAUSE)

01:18:53.680 --> 01:18:56.524
<i>Thank you.
Thank you so much.</i>

01:18:57.480 --> 01:19:02.168
Folks, I'll be signing books in the back,
but, please, no personalizations.

01:19:03.480 --> 01:19:05.323
I don't sign them all.

01:19:08.720 --> 01:19:10.051
(MOUTHING)

01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:18.126
Hi.

01:19:20.080 --> 01:19:21.969
(STAMMERING)
You're here.

01:19:22.040 --> 01:19:25.601
Well, I read a review of the book,
and I had to get my copy signed, so...

01:19:25.680 --> 01:19:27.364
Well, get in line.

01:19:27.440 --> 01:19:31.365
When I found that woman,
she was in the gutter.

01:19:31.720 --> 01:19:33.131
JUDITH: Thank you.

01:19:33.200 --> 01:19:34.645
WOMAN:
It's inspirational.

01:19:34.720 --> 01:19:39.408
Hey, do you want
to take a walk or...

01:19:39.480 --> 01:19:40.686
Yeah, yeah.

01:19:40.760 --> 01:19:41.761
Okay.

01:19:44.200 --> 01:19:45.565
(INAUDIBLE)

01:19:56.560 --> 01:19:58.369
(CHURCH BELL RINGING)

01:20:01.240 --> 01:20:04.130
When I was in the army,
I was a courier.

01:20:04.200 --> 01:20:05.531
Oh, yeah.

01:20:06.360 --> 01:20:09.807
And we were on a stopover
in the Azores.

01:20:09.880 --> 01:20:13.202
We were delivering a diplomatic
pouch or something to Prague.

01:20:15.080 --> 01:20:19.130
And the thing about
Portuguese whores

01:20:19.200 --> 01:20:23.569
is some are born in Portugal,
but some are born in Africa.

01:20:23.680 --> 01:20:25.205
It's a real mix.

01:20:28.240 --> 01:20:32.928
Anyway, I end up meeting
this great gal, Lydia.

01:20:33.760 --> 01:20:35.091
Local girl.

01:20:35.960 --> 01:20:38.725
